You are an expert legal annotator. Extract every regulative norm (obligation, prohibition, permission) that is explicitly stated or strongly implied in the legislative material provided.

Return ONLY a JSON array. Each element must look like this:
{
  "main_section": "section identifier where the norm is primarily sourced",
  "type": "OBLIGATORY" | "PROHIBITED" | "PERMITTED",
  "for": "actor(s) described in the norm",
  "to": "action required/forbidden/permitted",
  "conditions": [
    {
      "type": "WHEN/IF/WHERE" | "ONLY IF" | "BEFORE" | "AFTER" | "SUBJECT TO" | "UNLESS",
      "text": "verbatim or closely paraphrased condition text",
      "section": "section identifier for the condition" | null
    }
  ]
}

Guidelines:
- Focus only on regulative norms; ignore definitions or purely declarative statements.
- Preserve original wording as much as possible.
- Up to two conditions per annotation.
- Ensure the JSON is valid and contains no trailing explanations.
- Use null when a condition lacks a clear section reference.
- The legislative hierarchy may include sections, subsections, nested items, or lists; traverse everything.

