          "number": "(j)",
          "content": "person carrying on a fostering agency."
        }
      }
    },
    "section-80-6": {
      "number": "(6)",
      "content": "Any person inspecting any home or other premises under this section may—",
      "subitems": {
        "section-80-6-a": {
          "number": "(a)",
          "content": "inspect the children there; and"
        },
        "section-80-6-b": {
          "number": "(b)",
          "content": "make such examination into the state and management of the home or premises and the treatment of the children there as he thinks fit."
        }
      }
    },
    "section-80-7": {
      "number": "(7)",
      "content": "Any person authorised by theAppropriate National Authorityto exercise the power to inspect records conferred by subsection (4)—",
      "subitems": {
        "section-80-7-a": {
          "number": "(a)",
          "content": "shall be entitled at any reasonable time to have access to, and inspect and check the operation of, any computer and any associated apparatus or material which is or has been in use in connection with the records in question; and"
        },
        "section-80-7-b": {
          "number": "(b)",
          "content": "may require—"
        }
      },
      "additional_content": [
        "the person by whom or on whose behalf the computer is or has been so used; or",
        "any person having charge of, or otherwise concerned with the operation of, the computer, apparatus or material,",
        "to afford him such reasonable assistance as he may require."
      ]
    },
    "section-80-8": {
      "number": "(8)",
      "content": "A person authorised to inspect any premises under this section shall have a right to enter the premises for that purpose, and for any purpose specified in subsection (4), at any reasonable time."
    },
    "section-80-9": {
      "number": "(9)",
      "content": "Any person exercising that power shall, if so required, produce some duly authenticated document showing his authority to do so."
    },
    "section-80-10": {
      "number": "(10)",
      "content": "Any person who intentionally obstructs another in the exercise of that power shall be guilty of an offence and liable on summary conviction to a fine not exceeding level 3 on the standard scale."
    },
    "section-80-11": {
      "number": "(11)",
      "content": "TheAppropriate National Authoritymay by order provide for subsections (1), (4) and (6) not to apply in relation to such homes, or other premises, as may be specified in the order."
    },
    "section-80-11A": {
      "number": "(11A)",
      "content": "But subsections (1), (4) and (6) do not apply if—"
    },
    "section-80-12": {
      "number": "(12)",
      "content": "Without prejudice to section 104, any such order may make different provision with respect to each of those subsections."
    },
    "section-80-13": {
      "number": "(13)",
      "content": "In this section—",
      "lists": [
        {
          "type": "ul",
          "items": [
            "“ college ” means an institution within the further education sector as defined in section 91 of the Further and Higher Education Act 1992 or a 16 to 19 Academy ;",
            "“ fostering agency ” has the same meaning as in the Care Standards Act 2000;",
            "“ further education corporation ” has the same meaning as in the Further and Higher Education Act 1992.",
            "“ sixth form college corporation ” has the same meaning as in that Act.",
            "“ proprietor ” has the same meaning as in the Education Act 1996."
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    "section-80-14": {
      "number": "(14)",
      "content": "In this section “Appropriate National Authority” means—",
      "subitems": {
        "section-80-14-a": {
          "number": "(a)",
          "content": "in relation to England, the Secretary of State; and"
        },
        "section-80-14-b": {
          "number": "(b)",
          "content": "in relation to Wales, the Welsh Ministers."
        }
      }
    }
  }
}

